{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013EkKXUeMkigpHBQw7nheBm","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Specification: 101 Lord of the RNGs\n     2→\n     3→## Meta\n     4→\n     5→| Field | Value |\n     6→|-------|-------|\n     7→| Status | Ready |\n     8→| Priority | P0 |\n     9→| Phase | 2 |\n    10→| NR_OF_TRIES | 12 |\n    11→\n    12→---\n    13→\n    14→## Overview\n    15→\n    16→Lord of the RNGs is a winner-takes-all jackpot wheel game. Players stake SOL into tiered pools and can purchase multiple entries to increase their odds. A VRF-backed wheel spin selects one winner who claims the entire pot. Each tier operates independently with its own wheel, players, and prize pool.\n    17→\n    18→## User Stories\n    19→\n    20→- As a player, I want to buy entries into a jackpot wheel so that I have a chance at winning the entire pot.\n    21→- As a player, I want to buy multiple entries so that I can increase my odds of winning.\n    22→- As a player, I want to watch a wheel spin animation so that I experience the excitement of the draw.\n    23→- As a player, I want to see my odds reflected visually on the wheel so that I understand my chances.\n    24→\n    25→---\n    26→\n    27→## Scope Alignment\n    28→\n    29→- **`docs/SCOPE.md` references**: Section 2 (V1 In Scope: Lord of the RNGs), Section 5 (V1 Game Scope), Section 8 (Delivery Plan - Phase 2)\n    30→- **Scope status**: V1 In Scope\n    31→- **Phase boundary**: Phase 2 - Lord of the RNGs End-to-End\n    32→\n    33→## Required Context Files\n    34→\n    35→- `sources/rng-utopia/docs/LORD_OF_THE_RNGS.md` (game concept source)\n    36→- `sources/rng-utopia/docs/PLATFORM.md` (tier-based betting, platform fee, VRF)\n    37→\n    38→## Contract Files\n    39→\n    40→- `solana/programs/coinflip/` — reference program (same architecture pattern)\n    41→- `solana/shared/src/` — shared Rust crate (lifecycle, fees, tiers, escrow, vrf_orao, cpi, pause, timeout)\n    42→- `apps/platform/src/features/lord-of-rngs/` — existing frontend mock (types, components, context, mock-simulation)\n    43→- `packages/game-engine/src/types.ts` — tier amounts, fee constants\n    44→\n    45→---\n    46→\n    47→## Scope Decisions (Refinement)\n    48→\n    49→| Decision | Choice | Rationale |\n    50→|----------|--------|-----------|\n    51→| Tier amounts | SOL values from shared crate (0.005–1.0 SOL) | Same tiers as coinflip. Concept doc USD values are outdated. |\n    52→| Entry cap per player | No cap (whale-friendly) | Entries is a u32 counter per player — unbounded entries don't affect account size. |\n    53→| Max players per round | 20 | Vec\\<PlayerEntry\\> in round PDA. 20 × 36 bytes = ~720 bytes. Conservative for V1. |\n    54→| Account design | Vec in round PDA | Single account per round. Simpler than separate PDAs per player. Max 20 players enforced. |\n    55→| Spin trigger | \"Spin\" button + permissionless instruction | Button appears/enables after countdown expires. Any player can press it. On-chain instruction is idempotent (rejects if already Locked). All clients poll/subscribe for phase transition so UX updates as soon as anyone spins. |\n    56→| Claim model | Pull-based + frontend auto-send | On-chain: winner calls `claim_payout`. Frontend: auto-sends claim tx after win reveal. Consistent with coinflip/FOUNDATIONS.md. |\n    57→| Game discriminator | Add to platform CPI | Add `game_type` field to `update_player_profile`. Enables per-game stats for both coinflip and lord. |\n    58→| Audio (FR-8) | Deferred | No audio in 101 scope. Dedicated audio spec later (same decision as coinflip). |\n    59→| Visual pulse (FR-2.5) | Frontend-only | CSS animation for final 5 seconds of countdown. No on-chain involvement. |\n    60→\n    61→---\n    62→\n    63→## Functional Requirements\n    64→\n    65→### FR-1: Waiting Phase\n    66→\n    67→Round is open but waiting for minimum 2 players in a tier before countdown begins.\n    68→\n    69→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n    70→- [ ] Players can join and purchase entries during waiting\n    71→- [ ] No countdown timer yet\n    72→- [ ] Display shows current entries and pool size\n    73→- [ ] \"Waiting for players...\" message shown\n    74→- [ ] Countdown triggers when 2nd unique player joins (not just 2nd entry from same player)\n    75→\n    76→### FR-2: Countdown Phase (60 seconds)\n    77→\n    78→Active entry period with a visible countdown after minimum players reached.\n    79→\n    80→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n    81→- [ ] 60-second countdown begins when 2nd unique player joins\n    82→- [ ] Additional players can join during countdown (up to max 20)\n    83→- [ ] Existing players can purchase additional entries\n    84→- [ ] Pool size and entry count update in real-time\n    85→- [ ] Visual pulse in final 5 seconds of countdown <!-- deferred: audio ticks deferred to dedicated audio spec -->\n    86→\n    87→### FR-3: Entry Mechanics\n    88→\n    89→Players can purchase multiple entries per tier, each costing the tier amount in SOL.\n    90→\n    91→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n    92→- [ ] Each entry costs the tier amount (e.g., 1.0 SOL per entry in Diamond) <!-- resolved: SOL amounts from shared crate, not USD -->\n    93→- [ ] Players can purchase multiple entries in same tier\n    94→- [ ] Each entry = one slot on the wheel\n    95→- [ ] No maximum entry limit per player <!-- resolved: confirmed whale-friendly, entries is u32 counter -->\n    96→- [ ] player_win_probability = player_entries / total_entries\n    97→- [ ] Entries purchasable during Waiting and Countdown phases only\n    98→\n    99→### FR-4: Spin Phase\n   100→\n   101→VRF determines the winner. Any player can trigger the spin via a \"Spin\" button that enables after countdown expires.\n   102→\n   103→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   104→- [ ] Joins disabled when countdown reaches zero (on-chain phase enforcement)\n   105→- [ ] \"Spin\" button appears/enables for all players once countdown expires and phase is still Active\n   106→- [ ] Any player can send `start_spin` — instruction is idempotent (succeeds once, rejects if already Locked)\n   107→- [ ] All clients poll/subscribe for phase transition — UX updates for everyone as soon as anyone spins\n   108→- [ ] VRF selects winning slot (all slots have equal probability)\n   109→- [ ] Wheel spin animation with realistic physics (fast start, gradual slow)\n   110→- [ ] Winner = player who owns the selected slot (VRF result mod total_entries → slot → owner)\n   111→- [ ] Result is provably fair and verifiable\n   112→\n   113→### FR-5: Winner Determination and Payout\n   114→\n   115→Single winner takes the entire pot minus platform fee. Pull-based claim with frontend auto-send.\n   116→\n   117→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   118→- [ ] winner_payout = total_pool × 0.97 (3% platform fee)\n   119→- [ ] Single winner takes 97% of pool\n   120→- [ ] Payout recorded on-chain (via RoundSettled event)\n   121→- [ ] Winner can claim funds (pull-based `claim_payout` instruction)\n   122→- [ ] Settlement is idempotent (double-claim rejected, round account closed after claim)\n   123→\n   124→### FR-6: Tier Selection UI\n   125→\n   126→Overview of all six tiers with current state per tier.\n   127→\n   128→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   129→- [ ] Grid showing all six tiers\n   130→- [ ] Each tier card shows: name, entry cost, current phase, player count, total entries, pool size\n   131→- [ ] Countdown timer shown for tiers in Countdown phase\n   132→\n   133→### FR-7: Active Game UI (Wheel View)\n   134→\n   135→The wheel visualization and interaction controls.\n   136→\n   137→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   138→- [ ] Large wheel divided into slots\n   139→- [ ] Player's own slots highlighted in distinct color\n   140→- [ ] Entry count per player shown in legend\n   141→- [ ] \"Buy Entry\" button (disabled during Spin/Reveal/Complete)\n   142→- [ ] \"Spin\" button appears after countdown expires (disabled once spin starts or if phase already Locked)\n   143→- [ ] Current pool size prominently displayed\n   144→- [ ] Smooth spin animation with gradual deceleration\n   145→- [ ] Winner slot highlighted with glow and confetti\n   146→- [ ] \"YOU WON!\" overlay if current player wins\n   147→\n   148→### FR-8: Audio\n   149→\n   150→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   151→- [x] ~~Wheel spin sound (clicking/ticking)~~ [DEFERRED] <!-- deferred: audio integration deferred to dedicated audio spec -->\n   152→- [x] ~~Countdown beeps in final seconds~~ [DEFERRED] <!-- deferred: audio integration deferred to dedicated audio spec -->\n   153→- [x] ~~Dramatic drum roll during final spin moments~~ [DEFERRED] <!-- deferred: audio integration deferred to dedicated audio spec -->\n   154→- [x] ~~Victory fanfare for winner~~ [DEFERRED] <!-- deferred: audio integration deferred to dedicated audio spec -->\n   155→- [x] ~~Coin/cash sound for payout~~ [DEFERRED] <!-- deferred: audio integration deferred to dedicated audio spec -->\n   156→\n   157→### FR-9: Fairness Verification\n   158→\n   159→Each round includes VRF proof data for independent verification.\n   160→\n   161→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   162→- [ ] RoundSettled event emits VRF request key, randomness, winning slot, winner, payout\n   163→- [ ] Fairness page supports Lord of the RNGs verification (paste tx signature → re-derive winning slot from randomness)\n   164→- [ ] Active round sidebar shows seed hash (before spin) and VRF proof data (after settlement)\n   165→\n   166→---\n   167→\n   168→## Success Criteria\n   169→\n   170→- A player can buy entries, watch the spin, and the correct winner receives the full pot\n   171→- Multiple entries correctly increase win probability proportionally\n   172→- VRF-backed results are independently verifiable\n   173→- Per-tier independence: different tiers can be in different phases simultaneously\n   174→- Round lifecycle (waiting → countdown → spin) runs without manual intervention\n   175→\n   176→---\n   177→\n   178→## Dependencies\n   179→\n   180→- [x] VRF provider selected: Orao (per `docs/DECISIONS.md`)\n   181→- [x] Shared infrastructure (004): lifecycle, escrow, fees, vrf_orao, cpi, tiers, pause, timeout\n   182→- [x] Platform program: initialize_config, create_player_profile, update_player_profile\n   183→- [ ] Game discriminator added to platform CPI (part of this spec)\n   184→\n   185→## Assumptions\n   186→\n   187→- No entry cap per player (whale-friendly by design)\n   188→- Max 20 players per round (Vec<PlayerEntry> account size cap)\n   189→- Round only triggers countdown with minimum 2 unique players\n   190→- Each tier operates fully independently (separate round PDA per tier)\n   191→- This is the second V1 game after Coinflip\n   192→- SOL-denominated tiers (same amounts as coinflip: 0.005–1.0 SOL)\n   193→\n   194→---\n   195→\n   196→## Validation Plan\n   197→\n   198→| # | Acceptance Criterion | Validation Method | Evidence Required |\n   199→|---|---------------------|-------------------|-------------------|\n   200→| 1 | Multi-entry increases probability | Buy N entries, verify N/total shown | Probability display |\n   201→| 2 | VRF selects winner fairly | Verify VRF proof for winning slot | VRF proof + slot mapping |\n   202→| 3 | Payout = pool × 0.97 | Check on-chain settlement | On-chain balance assertions |\n   203→| 4 | Tiers operate independently | Two tiers in different phases | Bankrun test |\n   204→| 5 | Countdown triggers at 2 players | Join as 2nd player, verify countdown starts | Phase transition assertion |\n   205→| 6 | Max 20 players enforced | 21st player rejected | Bankrun error test |\n   206→| 7 | Pull-based claim works | Winner calls claim_payout, funds transfer | Bankrun balance assertion |\n   207→\n   208→---\n   209→\n   210→## Completion Signal\n   211→\n   212→### Implementation Checklist\n   213→\n   214→#### Phase A: On-Chain Program (Lord of the RNGs)\n   215→\n   216→- [x] [on-chain] Scaffold `solana/programs/lordofrngs/` — Cargo.toml, Xargo.toml, `src/lib.rs` with `declare_id!`, `src/state.rs` with `LordConfig` + `JackpotRound` + `PlayerEntry` + `RoundSettled` event, `src/error.rs` with error codes. Register in `solana/Cargo.toml` workspace members and `Anchor.toml` programs. Verify: `anchor build -p lordofrngs` succeeds. (done: iteration 1)\n   217→- [x] [on-chain] `initialize_config` instruction — admin creates `LordConfig` PDA (`[b\"lord_config\"]`) with treasury + authority + paused flag. Pattern: copy from coinflip `initialize_config.rs`. Verify: bankrun test creates config, reads back fields. (done: iteration 2)\n   218→- [x] [on-chain] `create_round` instruction — creates `JackpotRound` PDA (`[b\"jackpot_round\", tier, round_number]`). Caller pays rent and is first player. Sets phase=Waiting, records entry, transfers entry_amount lamports to round PDA escrow. Requires: config not paused, valid tier (0–5), round_number from a counter on LordConfig. Verify: bankrun test creates round, checks PDA data + escrow balance. (done: iteration 3)\n   219→- [x] [on-chain] `join_round` instruction — new player joins an existing round. Validates: phase is Waiting or Active (countdown), player not already in round, player count < 20. Adds PlayerEntry to Vec, transfers entry_amount × entries to escrow. If this is the 2nd unique player, transition phase Waiting→Active and set `countdown_ends_at = clock + 60`. Verify: bankrun tests for happy path (join triggers countdown), duplicate player rejection, max players rejection, wrong phase rejection. (done: iteration 4)\n   220→- [x] [on-chain] `buy_more_entries` instruction — existing player buys additional entries. Validates: phase is Waiting or Active, player already in round. Increments player's entry count, transfers entry_amount × entries to escrow. Verify: bankrun test buys more, checks updated entry count + pool. (done: iteration 5)\n   221→- [x] [on-chain] `start_spin` instruction — permissionless, idempotent. Validates: phase is Active, `clock.unix_timestamp >= countdown_ends_at`. If phase is already Locked, return Ok (idempotent no-op, no error). Transitions phase Active→Locked, requests Orao VRF (CPI). Records `vrf_request_key`. Verify: bankrun tests — happy path (phase transition + VRF request), idempotent re-call (no error when already Locked), too early rejection (countdown not expired), wrong phase rejection. (done: iteration 6)\n   222→- [x] [on-chain] `claim_payout` instruction — winner claims the pot. Reads Orao randomness, derives `winning_slot = randomness[0..8] as u64 % total_entries`, maps slot→winner. Calculates fee (3%) + net payout. Transfers fee to treasury, payout to winner. Closes round PDA (rent → round creator). CPI to platform `update_player_profile` for all players (winner gets +1 win, all get +1 game, wagered, won). Emits `RoundSettled` event. Verify: bankrun test — correct winner, correct payout, treasury fee, profile updates, idempotency (account closed after claim). (done: iteration 7)\n   223→- [x] [on-chain] `timeout_refund` instruction — permissionless. If phase is Locked and VRF not fulfilled after 2 minutes (`clock > locked_at + 120`), refund all players' entry amounts. Close round PDA. Verify: bankrun test with unfulfilled VRF. (done: iteration 8)\n   224→- [x] [on-chain] `force_close` instruction — admin-only. Closes a stuck round, refunds all players. Verify: bankrun test admin-only guard. (done: iteration 9)\n   225→\n   226→#### Phase B: Platform Program Update (Game Discriminator)\n   227→\n   228→- [x] [on-chain] Add `game_type: u8` parameter to platform `update_player_profile` instruction. Update shared CPI helper to pass game_type. Update coinflip `claim_payout` to pass `game_type = 0` (coinflip). Lord will pass `game_type = 1`. Verify: existing coinflip bankrun tests still pass, platform tests updated. (done: iteration 10)\n   229→\n   230→#### Phase C: Game Engine + Anchor Client\n   231→\n   232→- [x] [engine] Add `lordofrngs.ts` to `packages/game-engine/src/` — exports: `LORDOFRNGS_PROGRAM_ID`, `getRoundPda(tier, roundNumber)`, `getConfigPda()`, `determineWinnerFromRandomness(randomness, totalEntries, players)`, `mapSlotToPlayer(winningSlot, players)`. Verify: TypeScript compiles. (done: iteration 11)\n   233→- [x] [engine] Add Lord of the RNGs verification function to `packages/game-engine/src/` or `packages/fairness/src/` — given a tx signature, extract RoundSettled event, re-derive winning_slot from randomness, verify it matches the event's winner. Pattern: mirror coinflip `verification.ts`. Verify: TypeScript compiles. (done: iteration 12)\n   234→- [ ] [engine] Run `anchor build -p lordofrngs` and sync IDL to `packages/anchor-client/src/lordofrngs.json`. Export typed program interface from anchor-client package. Verify: `pnpm build:all` succeeds.\n   235→\n   236→#### Phase D: Frontend Wiring (Replace Mocks)\n   237→\n   238→- [ ] [frontend] Create `features/lord-of-rngs/utils/chain.ts` — real on-chain transaction builders and queries: `buildJoinRoundTx`, `buildBuyMoreEntriesTx`, `buildStartSpinTx`, `buildClaimPayoutTx`, `fetchRound`, `fetchAllTierRounds`, `fetchClaimableRounds`. Pattern: mirror coinflip `chain.ts`. Verify: TypeScript compiles.\n   239→- [ ] [frontend] Update `LordOfRngsContext.tsx` — replace mock-simulation imports with chain.ts calls. Wire `joinTierRound` → `buildJoinRoundTx` + `sendAndConfirm`. Wire `buyMoreEntriesAction` → `buildBuyMoreEntriesTx` + `sendAndConfirm`. Wire `claimPayout` → `buildClaimPayoutTx` + `sendAndConfirm` (auto-triggered on win). Add `startSpin` action → `buildStartSpinTx` + `sendAndConfirm` (triggered by \"Spin\" button). Poll/subscribe round account so all clients detect phase transition to Locked as soon as anyone spins (disable Spin button, start animation). Verify: TypeScript compiles, `pnpm lint` clean.\n   240→- [ ] [frontend] Update tier types — ensure `types.ts` uses SOL amounts (remove `$` comments). Ensure `TierLobby`, `ActiveRoundView`, `TierRoundView` display SOL values. Verify: `pnpm lint` clean.\n   241→- [ ] [frontend] Wire fairness verification — update sidebar fairness section to show real VRF data from RoundSettled event. Add Lord of the RNGs section to `/fairness` page (paste tx signature → verify winning slot). Verify: TypeScript compiles.\n   242→- [ ] [frontend] Delete `mock-simulation.ts` once all context actions use chain.ts. Verify: `pnpm build:all` succeeds, no imports of mock-simulation remain.\n   243→\n   244→#### Phase E: Testing\n   245→\n   246→- [ ] [test] Bankrun test suite for lord program — at minimum: initialize_config, create_round (happy + invalid tier), join_round (happy + triggers countdown + duplicate player + max players + wrong phase), buy_more_entries (happy + not in round + wrong phase), start_spin (happy + too early + wrong phase), claim_payout (correct winner + correct payout + fee to treasury + profile CPI + idempotent/closed), timeout_refund (happy + VRF fulfilled rejects + too early rejects), force_close (admin only). Target: ≥15 tests. Verify: `anchor test` passes.\n   247→- [ ] [test] Update visual baselines for Lord of the RNGs pages. Run `pnpm test:visual` to identify failures, then `pnpm test:visual:update` to regenerate. **Before committing**: read old baseline and new screenshot for each changed page (use Read tool on PNG files). Evaluate:\n   248→  - **PASS** (changes clearly match spec intent, only expected areas changed) → commit updated baselines\n   249→  - **REVIEW** (changes look plausible but unexpected areas also changed, or uncertain) → do NOT commit baselines. Save the diff images from `test-results/` to `docs/specs/101-lord-of-the-rngs/visual-review/`, describe concerns in `history.md`, output `<blocker>Visual review needed: [describe what looks off]</blocker>`\n   250→  - **FAIL** (layout broken, elements missing, clearly wrong) → fix the code, do NOT update baselines\n   251→- [ ] [test] Add local deterministic E2E coverage in `e2e/local/` — at minimum: smoke test (app loads with lord page), lifecycle test (Player A creates round → Player B joins → countdown → start_spin → VRF fulfilled → claim → payout verified on-chain). Requires: localnet-bootstrap.sh updated with lordofrngs program + mock VRF accounts. Verify: `pnpm test:e2e` passes.\n   252→- [ ] [test] Add devnet real-VRF E2E coverage in `e2e/devnet/` — lifecycle test with real Orao VRF fulfillment. Pattern: mirror coinflip devnet lifecycle test with `pollVrfFulfillment` + `waitForResult`. Verify: code compiles and type-checks (actual run requires devnet deploy).\n   253→\n   254→#### Phase F: Validation\n   255→\n   256→- [ ] [test] All existing tests pass (coinflip bankrun, platform bankrun, visual regression, lint, typecheck)\n   257→- [ ] [test] Lord bankrun tests pass (≥15 tests)\n   258→- [ ] [test] `pnpm lint` clean, `pnpm build:all` succeeds\n   259→- [ ] [test] No JS console errors on Lord of the RNGs pages\n   260→- [ ] [test] All FR acceptance criteria verified (FR-1 through FR-7, FR-9)\n   261→\n   262→### Iteration Instructions\n   263→\n   264→If ANY check fails:\n   265→1. Identify the specific issue\n   266→2. Fix the code\n   267→3. Re-run tests\n   268→4. Re-verify all criteria\n   269→5. Check again\n   270→\n   271→**Only when ALL checks pass, output:** `<promise>DONE</promise>`\n   272→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f4281aa2-334c-41cb-8346-1f9da2569415","uuid":"bed1045b-b240-4900-8cdc-f9cbc8db3029","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/101-lord-of-the-rngs/spec.md","content":"# Specification: 101 Lord of the RNGs\n\n## Meta\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| Status | Ready |\n| Priority | P0 |\n| Phase | 2 |\n| NR_OF_TRIES | 12 |\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nLord of the RNGs is a winner-takes-all jackpot wheel game. Players stake SOL into tiered pools and can purchase multiple entries to increase their odds. A VRF-backed wheel spin selects one winner who claims the entire pot. Each tier operates independently with its own wheel, players, and prize pool.\n\n## User Stories\n\n- As a player, I want to buy entries into a jackpot wheel so that I have a chance at winning the entire pot.\n- As a player, I want to buy multiple entries so that I can increase my odds of winning.\n- As a player, I want to watch a wheel spin animation so that I experience the excitement of the draw.\n- As a player, I want to see my odds reflected visually on the wheel so that I understand my chances.\n\n---\n\n## Scope Alignment\n\n- **`docs/SCOPE.md` references**: Section 2 (V1 In Scope: Lord of the RNGs), Section 5 (V1 Game Scope), Section 8 (Delivery Plan - Phase 2)\n- **Scope status**: V1 In Scope\n- **Phase boundary**: Phase 2 - Lord of the RNGs End-to-End\n\n## Required Context Files\n\n- `sources/rng-utopia/docs/LORD_OF_THE_RNGS.md` (game concept source)\n- `sources/rng-utopia/docs/PLATFORM.md` (tier-based betting, platform fee, VRF)\n\n## Contract Files\n\n- `solana/programs/coinflip/` — reference program (same architecture pattern)\n- `solana/shared/src/` — shared Rust crate (lifecycle, fees, tiers, escrow, vrf_orao, cpi, pause, timeout)\n- `apps/platform/src/features/lord-of-rngs/` — existing frontend mock (types, components, context, mock-simulation)\n- `packages/game-engine/src/types.ts` — tier amounts, fee constants\n\n---\n\n## Scope Decisions (Refinement)\n\n| Decision | Choice | Rationale |\n|----------|--------|-----------|\n| Tier amounts | SOL values from shared crate (0.005–1.0 SOL) | Same tiers as coinflip. Concept doc USD values are outdated. |\n| Entry cap per player | No cap (whale-friendly) | Entries is a u32 counter per player — unbounded entries don't affect account size. |\n| Max players per round | 20 | Vec\\<PlayerEntry\\> in round PDA. 20 × 36 bytes = ~720 bytes. Conservative for V1. |\n| Account design | Vec in round PDA | Single account per round. Simpler than separate PDAs per player. Max 20 players enforced. |\n| Spin trigger | \"Spin\" button + permissionless instruction | Button appears/enables after countdown expires. Any player can press it. On-chain instruction is idempotent (rejects if already Locked). All clients poll/subscribe for phase transition so UX updates as soon as anyone spins. |\n| Claim model | Pull-based + frontend auto-send | On-chain: winner calls `claim_payout`. Frontend: auto-sends claim tx after win reveal. Consistent with coinflip/FOUNDATIONS.md. |\n| Game discriminator | Add to platform CPI | Add `game_type` field to `update_player_profile`. Enables per-game stats for both coinflip and lord. |\n| Audio (FR-8) | Deferred | No audio in 101 scope. Dedicated audio spec later (same decision as coinflip). |\n| Visual pulse (FR-2.5) | Frontend-only | CSS animation for final 5 seconds of countdown. No on-chain involvement. |\n\n---\n\n## Functional Requirements\n\n### FR-1: Waiting Phase\n\nRound is open but waiting for minimum 2 players in a tier before countdown begins.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Players can join and purchase entries during waiting\n- [ ] No countdown timer yet\n- [ ] Display shows current entries and pool size\n- [ ] \"Waiting for players...\" message shown\n- [ ] Countdown triggers when 2nd unique player joins (not just 2nd entry from same player)\n\n### FR-2: Countdown Phase (60 seconds)\n\nActive entry period with a visible countdown after minimum players reached.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] 60-second countdown begins when 2nd unique player joins\n- [ ] Additional players can join during countdown (up to max 20)\n- [ ] Existing players can purchase additional entries\n- [ ] Pool size and entry count update in real-time\n- [ ] Visual pulse in final 5 seconds of countdown <!-- deferred: audio ticks deferred to dedicated audio spec -->\n\n### FR-3: Entry Mechanics\n\nPlayers can purchase multiple entries per tier, each costing the tier amount in SOL.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Each entry costs the tier amount (e.g., 1.0 SOL per entry in Diamond) <!-- resolved: SOL amounts from shared crate, not USD -->\n- [ ] Players can purchase multiple entries in same tier\n- [ ] Each entry = one slot on the wheel\n- [ ] No maximum entry limit per player <!-- resolved: confirmed whale-friendly, entries is u32 counter -->\n- [ ] player_win_probability = player_entries / total_entries\n- [ ] Entries purchasable during Waiting and Countdown phases only\n\n### FR-4: Spin Phase\n\nVRF determines the winner. Any player can trigger the spin via a \"Spin\" button that enables after countdown expires.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Joins disabled when countdown reaches zero (on-chain phase enforcement)\n- [ ] \"Spin\" button appears/enables for all players once countdown expires and phase is still Active\n- [ ] Any player can send `start_spin` — instruction is idempotent (succeeds once, rejects if already Locked)\n- [ ] All clients poll/subscribe for phase transition — UX updates for everyone as soon as anyone spins\n- [ ] VRF selects winning slot (all slots have equal probability)\n- [ ] Wheel spin animation with realistic physics (fast start, gradual slow)\n- [ ] Winner = player who owns the selected slot (VRF result mod total_entries → slot → owner)\n- [ ] Result is provably fair and verifiable\n\n### FR-5: Winner Determination and Payout\n\nSingle winner takes the entire pot minus platform fee. Pull-based claim with frontend auto-send.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] winner_payout = total_pool × 0.97 (3% platform fee)\n- [ ] Single winner takes 97% of pool\n- [ ] Payout recorded on-chain (via RoundSettled event)\n- [ ] Winner can claim funds (pull-based `claim_payout` instruction)\n- [ ] Settlement is idempotent (double-claim rejected, round account closed after claim)\n\n### FR-6: Tier Selection UI\n\nOverview of all six tiers with current state per tier.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Grid showing all six tiers\n- [ ] Each tier card shows: name, entry cost, current phase, player count, total entries, pool size\n- [ ] Countdown timer shown for tiers in Countdown phase\n\n### FR-7: Active Game UI (Wheel View)\n\nThe wheel visualization and interaction controls.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Large wheel divided into slots\n- [ ] Player's own slots highlighted in distinct color\n- [ ] Entry count per player shown in legend\n- [ ] \"Buy Entry\" button (disabled during Spin/Reveal/Complete)\n- [ ] \"Spin\" button appears after countdown expires (disabled once spin starts or if phase already Locked)\n- [ ] Current pool size prominently displayed\n- [ ] Smooth spin animation with gradual deceleration\n- [ ] Winner slot highlighted with glow and confetti\n- [ ] \"YOU WON!\" overlay if current player wins\n\n### FR-8: Audio\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [x] ~~Wheel spin sound (clicking/ticking)~~ [DEFERRED] <!-- deferred: audio integration deferred to dedicated audio spec -->\n- [x] ~~Countdown beeps in final seconds~~ [DEFERRED] <!-- deferred: audio integration deferred to dedicated audio spec -->\n- [x] ~~Dramatic drum roll during final spin moments~~ [DEFERRED] <!-- deferred: audio integration deferred to dedicated audio spec -->\n- [x] ~~Victory fanfare for winner~~ [DEFERRED] <!-- deferred: audio integration deferred to dedicated audio spec -->\n- [x] ~~Coin/cash sound for payout~~ [DEFERRED] <!-- deferred: audio integration deferred to dedicated audio spec -->\n\n### FR-9: Fairness Verification\n\nEach round includes VRF proof data for independent verification.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] RoundSettled event emits VRF request key, randomness, winning slot, winner, payout\n- [ ] Fairness page supports Lord of the RNGs verification (paste tx signature → re-derive winning slot from randomness)\n- [ ] Active round sidebar shows seed hash (before spin) and VRF proof data (after settlement)\n\n---\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- A player can buy entries, watch the spin, and the correct winner receives the full pot\n- Multiple entries correctly increase win probability proportionally\n- VRF-backed results are independently verifiable\n- Per-tier independence: different tiers can be in different phases simultaneously\n- Round lifecycle (waiting → countdown → spin) runs without manual intervention\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- [x] VRF provider selected: Orao (per `docs/DECISIONS.md`)\n- [x] Shared infrastructure (004): lifecycle, escrow, fees, vrf_orao, cpi, tiers, pause, timeout\n- [x] Platform program: initialize_config, create_player_profile, update_player_profile\n- [ ] Game discriminator added to platform CPI (part of this spec)\n\n## Assumptions\n\n- No entry cap per player (whale-friendly by design)\n- Max 20 players per round (Vec<PlayerEntry> account size cap)\n- Round only triggers countdown with minimum 2 unique players\n- Each tier operates fully independently (separate round PDA per tier)\n- This is the second V1 game after Coinflip\n- SOL-denominated tiers (same amounts as coinflip: 0.005–1.0 SOL)\n\n---\n\n## Validation Plan\n\n| # | Acceptance Criterion | Validation Method | Evidence Required |\n|---|---------------------|-------------------|-------------------|\n| 1 | Multi-entry increases probability | Buy N entries, verify N/total shown | Probability display |\n| 2 | VRF selects winner fairly | Verify VRF proof for winning slot | VRF proof + slot mapping |\n| 3 | Payout = pool × 0.97 | Check on-chain settlement | On-chain balance assertions |\n| 4 | Tiers operate independently | Two tiers in different phases | Bankrun test |\n| 5 | Countdown triggers at 2 players | Join as 2nd player, verify countdown starts | Phase transition assertion |\n| 6 | Max 20 players enforced | 21st player rejected | Bankrun error test |\n| 7 | Pull-based claim works | Winner calls claim_payout, funds transfer | Bankrun balance assertion |\n\n---\n\n## Completion Signal\n\n### Implementation Checklist\n\n#### Phase A: On-Chain Program (Lord of the RNGs)\n\n- [x] [on-chain] Scaffold `solana/programs/lordofrngs/` — Cargo.toml, Xargo.toml, `src/lib.rs` with `declare_id!`, `src/state.rs` with `LordConfig` + `JackpotRound` + `PlayerEntry` + `RoundSettled` event, `src/error.rs` with error codes. Register in `solana/Cargo.toml` workspace members and `Anchor.toml` programs. Verify: `anchor build -p lordofrngs` succeeds. (done: iteration 1)\n- [x] [on-chain] `initialize_config` instruction — admin creates `LordConfig` PDA (`[b\"lord_config\"]`) with treasury + authority + paused flag. Pattern: copy from coinflip `initialize_config.rs`. Verify: bankrun test creates config, reads back fields. (done: iteration 2)\n- [x] [on-chain] `create_round` instruction — creates `JackpotRound` PDA (`[b\"jackpot_round\", tier, round_number]`). Caller pays rent and is first player. Sets phase=Waiting, records entry, transfers entry_amount lamports to round PDA escrow. Requires: config not paused, valid tier (0–5), round_number from a counter on LordConfig. Verify: bankrun test creates round, checks PDA data + escrow balance. (done: iteration 3)\n- [x] [on-chain] `join_round` instruction — new player joins an existing round. Validates: phase is Waiting or Active (countdown), player not already in round, player count < 20. Adds PlayerEntry to Vec, transfers entry_amount × entries to escrow. If this is the 2nd unique player, transition phase Waiting→Active and set `countdown_ends_at = clock + 60`. Verify: bankrun tests for happy path (join triggers countdown), duplicate player rejection, max players rejection, wrong phase rejection. (done: iteration 4)\n- [x] [on-chain] `buy_more_entries` instruction — existing player buys additional entries. Validates: phase is Waiting or Active, player already in round. Increments player's entry count, transfers entry_amount × entries to escrow. Verify: bankrun test buys more, checks updated entry count + pool. (done: iteration 5)\n- [x] [on-chain] `start_spin` instruction — permissionless, idempotent. Validates: phase is Active, `clock.unix_timestamp >= countdown_ends_at`. If phase is already Locked, return Ok (idempotent no-op, no error). Transitions phase Active→Locked, requests Orao VRF (CPI). Records `vrf_request_key`. Verify: bankrun tests — happy path (phase transition + VRF request), idempotent re-call (no error when already Locked), too early rejection (countdown not expired), wrong phase rejection. (done: iteration 6)\n- [x] [on-chain] `claim_payout` instruction — winner claims the pot. Reads Orao randomness, derives `winning_slot = randomness[0..8] as u64 % total_entries`, maps slot→winner. Calculates fee (3%) + net payout. Transfers fee to treasury, payout to winner. Closes round PDA (rent → round creator). CPI to platform `update_player_profile` for all players (winner gets +1 win, all get +1 game, wagered, won). Emits `RoundSettled` event. Verify: bankrun test — correct winner, correct payout, treasury fee, profile updates, idempotency (account closed after claim). (done: iteration 7)\n- [x] [on-chain] `timeout_refund` instruction — permissionless. If phase is Locked and VRF not fulfilled after 2 minutes (`clock > locked_at + 120`), refund all players' entry amounts. Close round PDA. Verify: bankrun test with unfulfilled VRF. (done: iteration 8)\n- [x] [on-chain] `force_close` instruction — admin-only. Closes a stuck round, refunds all players. Verify: bankrun test admin-only guard. (done: iteration 9)\n\n#### Phase B: Platform Program Update (Game Discriminator)\n\n- [x] [on-chain] Add `game_type: u8` parameter to platform `update_player_profile` instruction. Update shared CPI helper to pass game_type. Update coinflip `claim_payout` to pass `game_type = 0` (coinflip). Lord will pass `game_type = 1`. Verify: existing coinflip bankrun tests still pass, platform tests updated. (done: iteration 10)\n\n#### Phase C: Game Engine + Anchor Client\n\n- [x] [engine] Add `lordofrngs.ts` to `packages/game-engine/src/` — exports: `LORDOFRNGS_PROGRAM_ID`, `getRoundPda(tier, roundNumber)`, `getConfigPda()`, `determineWinnerFromRandomness(randomness, totalEntries, players)`, `mapSlotToPlayer(winningSlot, players)`. Verify: TypeScript compiles. (done: iteration 11)\n- [x] [engine] Add Lord of the RNGs verification function to `packages/game-engine/src/` or `packages/fairness/src/` — given a tx signature, extract RoundSettled event, re-derive winning_slot from randomness, verify it matches the event's winner. Pattern: mirror coinflip `verification.ts`. Verify: TypeScript compiles. (done: iteration 12)\n- [ ] [engine] Run `anchor build -p lordofrngs` and sync IDL to `packages/anchor-client/src/lordofrngs.json`. Export typed program interface from anchor-client package. Verify: `pnpm build:all` succeeds.\n\n#### Phase D: Frontend Wiring (Replace Mocks)\n\n- [ ] [frontend] Create `features/lord-of-rngs/utils/chain.ts` — real on-chain transaction builders and queries: `buildJoinRoundTx`, `buildBuyMoreEntriesTx`, `buildStartSpinTx`, `buildClaimPayoutTx`, `fetchRound`, `fetchAllTierRounds`, `fetchClaimableRounds`. Pattern: mirror coinflip `chain.ts`. Verify: TypeScript compiles.\n- [ ] [frontend] Update `LordOfRngsContext.tsx` — replace mock-simulation imports with chain.ts calls. Wire `joinTierRound` → `buildJoinRoundTx` + `sendAndConfirm`. Wire `buyMoreEntriesAction` → `buildBuyMoreEntriesTx` + `sendAndConfirm`. Wire `claimPayout` → `buildClaimPayoutTx` + `sendAndConfirm` (auto-triggered on win). Add `startSpin` action → `buildStartSpinTx` + `sendAndConfirm` (triggered by \"Spin\" button). Poll/subscribe round account so all clients detect phase transition to Locked as soon as anyone spins (disable Spin button, start animation). Verify: TypeScript compiles, `pnpm lint` clean.\n- [ ] [frontend] Update tier types — ensure `types.ts` uses SOL amounts (remove `$` comments). Ensure `TierLobby`, `ActiveRoundView`, `TierRoundView` display SOL values. Verify: `pnpm lint` clean.\n- [ ] [frontend] Wire fairness verification — update sidebar fairness section to show real VRF data from RoundSettled event. Add Lord of the RNGs section to `/fairness` page (paste tx signature → verify winning slot). Verify: TypeScript compiles.\n- [ ] [frontend] Delete `mock-simulation.ts` once all context actions use chain.ts. Verify: `pnpm build:all` succeeds, no imports of mock-simulation remain.\n\n#### Phase E: Testing\n\n- [ ] [test] Bankrun test suite for lord program — at minimum: initialize_config, create_round (happy + invalid tier), join_round (happy + triggers countdown + duplicate player + max players + wrong phase), buy_more_entries (happy + not in round + wrong phase), start_spin (happy + too early + wrong phase), claim_payout (correct winner + correct payout + fee to treasury + profile CPI + idempotent/closed), timeout_refund (happy + VRF fulfilled rejects + too early rejects), force_close (admin only). Target: ≥15 tests. Verify: `anchor test` passes.\n- [ ] [test] Update visual baselines for Lord of the RNGs pages. Run `pnpm test:visual` to identify failures, then `pnpm test:visual:update` to regenerate. **Before committing**: read old baseline and new screenshot for each changed page (use Read tool on PNG files). Evaluate:\n  - **PASS** (changes clearly match spec intent, only expected areas changed) → commit updated baselines\n  - **REVIEW** (changes look plausible but unexpected areas also changed, or uncertain) → do NOT commit baselines. Save the diff images from `test-results/` to `docs/specs/101-lord-of-the-rngs/visual-review/`, describe concerns in `history.md`, output `<blocker>Visual review needed: [describe what looks off]</blocker>`\n  - **FAIL** (layout broken, elements missing, clearly wrong) → fix the code, do NOT update baselines\n- [ ] [test] Add local deterministic E2E coverage in `e2e/local/` — at minimum: smoke test (app loads with lord page), lifecycle test (Player A creates round → Player B joins → countdown → start_spin → VRF fulfilled → claim → payout verified on-chain). Requires: localnet-bootstrap.sh updated with lordofrngs program + mock VRF accounts. Verify: `pnpm test:e2e` passes.\n- [ ] [test] Add devnet real-VRF E2E coverage in `e2e/devnet/` — lifecycle test with real Orao VRF fulfillment. Pattern: mirror coinflip devnet lifecycle test with `pollVrfFulfillment` + `waitForResult`. Verify: code compiles and type-checks (actual run requires devnet deploy).\n\n#### Phase F: Validation\n\n- [ ] [test] All existing tests pass (coinflip bankrun, platform bankrun, visual regression, lint, typecheck)\n- [ ] [test] Lord bankrun tests pass (≥15 tests)\n- [ ] [test] `pnpm lint` clean, `pnpm build:all` succeeds\n- [ ] [test] No JS console errors on Lord of the RNGs pages\n- [ ] [test] All FR acceptance criteria verified (FR-1 through FR-7, FR-9)\n\n### Iteration Instructions\n\nIf ANY check fails:\n1. Identify the specific issue\n2. Fix the code\n3. Re-run tests\n4. Re-verify all criteria\n5. Check again\n\n**Only when ALL checks pass, output:** `<promise>DONE</promise>`\n","numLines":272,"startLine":1,"totalLines":272}}}
