{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013FAwfsoCjZigwnK2PXyARE","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have comprehensive information. Let me create a final detailed summary document:\n\n## Comprehensive Exploration Report: anchor-client Package\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/`, here's the complete picture:\n\n### 1. **Directory Structure (Complete File Tree)**\n\n```\npackages/anchor-client/\n├── package.json              (package metadata, exports config)\n├── tsconfig.json            (TypeScript configuration)\n├── eslint.config.js         (ESLint rules, inherits from @rng-utopia/config)\n└── src/\n    ├── index.ts             (10 lines - main export hub)\n    ├── coinflip.ts          (936 lines - type definitions)\n    ├── coinflip.json        (929 lines - runtime IDL JSON)\n    ├── platform.ts          (344 lines - type definitions)\n    └── platform.json        (337 lines - runtime IDL JSON)\n```\n\n**Total source code**: 2,556 lines (936 + 344 + 929 + 337 + 10 = actual code/types)\n\n### 2. **Package.json Configuration**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"@rng-utopia/anchor-client\",\n  \"version\": \"0.1.0\",\n  \"private\": true,\n  \"type\": \"module\",                    // ES module, not CommonJS\n  \"main\": \"./src/index.ts\",           // Entry point targets source (no build step)\n  \"types\": \"./src/index.ts\",          // Same as main\n  \"exports\": {\n    \".\": \"./src/index.ts\"             // Single export path\n  },\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"lint\": \"eslint .\",\n    \"lint:fix\": \"eslint . --fix\",\n    \"typecheck\": \"tsc --noEmit\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest --passWithNoTests\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"@coral-xyz/anchor\": \"^0.32.1\",\n    \"@solana/web3.js\": \"^1.98.0\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@rng-utopia/config\": \"workspace:*\",\n    \"@types/node\": \"^22.10.0\",\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.7.0\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^2.1.0\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Key Points**:\n- **No build step** — TypeScript is compiled by consumers (src/ is directly exported)\n- **Workspace dependency** — works within the monorepo via turborepo\n- **Simple**: Only two dependencies beyond types (@coral-xyz/anchor, @solana/web3.js)\n\n### 3. **Index.ts - The Export Hub**\n\n```typescript\n// IDL JSON (runtime values)\nimport CoinflipIDL from \"./coinflip.json\" with { type: \"json\" };\nimport PlatformIDL from \"./platform.json\" with { type: \"json\" };\n\n// Type-safe IDL types (compile-time)\nexport type { Coinflip } from \"./coinflip.js\";\nexport type { Platform } from \"./platform.js\";\n\n// Re-export IDLs as typed constants\nexport { CoinflipIDL, PlatformIDL };\n```\n\n**Pattern Explanation**:\n- **`.json` with `{ type: \"json\" }`** — Node 24+ assertion syntax for JSON imports (static typing)\n- **`.js` imports for types** — Uses `.js` extension to reference `.ts` files (ESM resolution)\n- **Dual export** — Both runtime IDL JSON objects AND compile-time TypeScript types\n\n### 4. **IDL File Format (coinflip.json as example)**\n\nStructure is auto-generated by Anchor from the Rust program:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"address\": \"BdHFeqmkYe7znXV1Avk3zz496Pjo8QhEDN4MKPUTAWwx\",  // Program ID\n  \"metadata\": {\n    \"name\": \"coinflip\",\n    \"version\": \"0.1.0\",\n    \"spec\": \"0.1.0\"\n  },\n  \"instructions\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"cancelMatch\",              // camelCase (auto-converted from Rust)\n      \"discriminator\": [142, 136, ...],   // 8-byte instruction ID\n      \"accounts\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"creator\",\n          \"docs\": [\"...\"],\n          \"writable\": true,\n          \"signer\": true,\n          \"pda\": {\n            \"seeds\": [\n              { \"kind\": \"const\", \"value\": [109, 97, 116, 99, 104] },  // \"match\"\n              { \"kind\": \"account\", \"path\": \"creator\" }\n            ]\n          }\n        },\n        // ... more accounts\n      ],\n      \"args\": [\n        { \"name\": \"tier\", \"type\": \"u8\" },\n        { \"name\": \"side\", \"type\": \"u8\" }\n      ]\n    },\n    // ... more instructions\n  ],\n  \"accounts\": [\n    { \"name\": \"coinflipConfig\", \"discriminator\": [...] },\n    { \"name\": \"coinflipMatch\", \"discriminator\": [...] }\n  ],\n  \"events\": [\n    { \"name\": \"matchSettled\", \"discriminator\": [...] }\n  ],\n  \"errors\": [\n    {\n      \"code\": 6100,\n      \"name\": \"invalidSide\",\n      \"msg\": \"Invalid side: must be 0 (Heads) or 1 (Tails)\"\n    }\n    // ... more errors\n  ],\n  \"types\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"coinflipConfig\",\n      \"docs\": [\"Global configuration for the coinflip program.\"],\n      \"type\": {\n        \"kind\": \"struct\",\n        \"fields\": [\n          { \"name\": \"authority\", \"type\": \"pubkey\" },\n          { \"name\": \"treasury\", \"type\": \"pubkey\" },\n          // ... more fields\n        ]\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n### 5. **TypeScript Type Files (coinflip.ts structure)**\n\n```typescript\n/**\n * Program IDL in camelCase format in order to be used in JS/TS.\n *\n * Note that this is only a type helper and is not the actual IDL. The original\n * IDL can be found at `target/idl/coinflip.json`.\n */\nexport type Coinflip = {\n  \"address\": \"BdHFeqmkYe7znXV1Avk3zz496Pjo8QhEDN4MKPUTAWwx\",\n  \"metadata\": { ... },\n  \"instructions\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"cancelMatch\",\n      \"discriminator\": [142, 136, 247, ...],\n      \"accounts\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"creator\",\n          \"docs\": [\"The creator cancelling their match.\"],\n          \"writable\": true,\n          \"signer\": true\n        },\n        // ... 3 accounts total\n      ],\n      \"args\": []\n    },\n    // ... 7 instructions total (cancelMatch, claimPayout, createMatch, forceClose, initializeConfig, joinMatch, timeoutCancel)\n  ],\n  \"accounts\": [\n    { \"name\": \"coinflipConfig\", \"discriminator\": [...] },\n    { \"name\": \"coinflipMatch\", \"discriminator\": [...] }\n  ],\n  \"events\": [\n    { \"name\": \"matchSettled\", \"discriminator\": [...] }\n  ],\n  \"errors\": [\n    { \"code\": 6100, \"name\": \"invalidSide\", \"msg\": \"...\" },\n    // ... 11 total errors (codes 6100-6111)\n  ],\n  \"types\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"coinflipConfig\",\n      \"type\": {\n        \"kind\": \"struct\",\n        \"fields\": [\n          { \"name\": \"authority\", \"type\": \"pubkey\" },\n          { \"name\": \"treasury\", \"type\": \"pubkey\" },\n          { \"name\": \"paused\", \"type\": \"bool\" },\n          { \"name\": \"bump\", \"type\": \"u8\" }\n        ]\n      }\n    },\n    // ... 3 more types (coinflipMatch, matchSettled, roundPhase)\n  ]\n};\n```\n\n**Key characteristics**:\n- **Pure TypeScript type** (no `declare` or `const`)\n- **Mirrors JSON structure** — maps Anchor IDL to TS objects\n- **camelCase conversion** — Rust `cancel_match` → TypeScript `cancelMatch`\n- **Generated by Anchor** — not manually written (from `solana/target/types/`)\n\n### 6. **TypeScript Configuration (tsconfig.json)**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"extends\": \"@rng-utopia/config/tsconfig.base.json\",\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\n    \"types\": [\"node\"]\n  },\n  \"include\": [\"src\"]\n}\n```\n\n**Minimal config** — inherits all settings from the shared `@rng-utopia/config` package.\n\n### 7. **Build & Deployment Pipeline**\n\n**The complete workflow**:\n\n1. **Rust Program → IDL Generation** (in `solana/` workspace)\n   ```bash\n   cd solana && anchor build\n   # Outputs: solana/target/idl/*.json and solana/target/types/*.ts\n   ```\n\n2. **IDL Sync** (manual step via `scripts/sync-idl`)\n   ```bash\n   ./scripts/sync-idl\n   # Copies:\n   #   solana/target/idl/*.json → packages/anchor-client/src/\n   #   solana/target/types/*.ts → packages/anchor-client/src/\n   ```\n   \n   Script location: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/scripts/sync-idl`\n\n3. **Package Consumption** (by apps/platform and e2e tests)\n   ```typescript\n   import { CoinflipIDL, type Coinflip } from \"@rng-utopia/anchor-client\";\n   \n   // Create typed Program instance\n   const program = new Program(CoinflipIDL as Idl as Coinflip, provider);\n   ```\n\n### 8. **How Coinflip IDL is Exported (Complete Pattern)**\n\n**File: `packages/anchor-client/src/index.ts`**\n```typescript\nimport CoinflipIDL from \"./coinflip.json\" with { type: \"json\" };\nexport type { Coinflip } from \"./coinflip.js\";\nexport { CoinflipIDL };\n```\n\n**Consumers import like this:**\n```typescript\nimport { CoinflipIDL, type Coinflip } from \"@rng-utopia/anchor-client\";\n\n// IDL object (runtime, plain JavaScript)\nconst COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(CoinflipIDL.address);\n\n// Type for type-safe program interface\nconst program = new Program<Coinflip>(CoinflipIDL as Idl, provider);\n```\n\n**Three-part structure**:\n1. **IDL JSON file** — runtime configuration (instruction names, accounts, types)\n2. **TypeScript type file** — compile-time types for type safety\n3. **Re-export hub** — single import point for consumers\n\n### 9. **Real-World Consumer Example**\n\nFrom `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts`:\n```typescript\nimport { CoinflipIDL, type Coinflip } from \"@rng-utopia/anchor-client\";\nimport { Program, AnchorProvider, type Idl } from \"@coral-xyz/anchor\";\n\nconst COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(\n  import.meta.env.VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID ?? CoinflipIDL.address\n);\n\nexport function getCoinflipProgram(provider: AnchorProvider): Program<Coinflip> {\n  return new Program(CoinflipIDL as Idl as Coinflip, provider);\n}\n```\n\nThis pattern allows:\n- **Runtime flexibility** — read program ID from IDL if not env-overridden\n- **Type safety** — Anchor's `Program<Coinflip>` enforces correct instruction/account names\n- **IDE autocomplete** — TypeScript knows all instruction methods and their signatures\n\n### 10. **IDL Files Currently in Package**\n\n| File | Lines | Program | Address |\n|------|-------|---------|---------|\n| `coinflip.json` | 929 | coinflip | `BdHFeqmkYe7znXV1Avk3zz496Pjo8QhEDN4MKPUTAWwx` |\n| `coinflip.ts` | 936 | coinflip | (same address) |\n| `platform.json` | 337 | platform | `85qwC1cDpSYkBBHUcN4nuZ119hCx4N94X38GjAHxnWjA` |\n| `platform.ts` | 344 | platform | (same address) |\n| **lordofrngs** | **Missing** | lordofrngs | `B9Lufh9GvuucDxDRZBr3qPNe4cJaS5MQBQKZxgUT5qYa` |\n\n**Note**: The `lordofrngs` program exists in the Anchor workspace and has generated IDL at `solana/target/idl/lordofrngs.json` (1156 lines) and `solana/target/types/lordofrngs.ts`, but these files have NOT YET been synced to `packages/anchor-client/src/`.\n\n### Summary: Replication Pattern for lordofrngs\n\nTo replicate this pattern for lordofrngs:\n\n1. **Ensure Anchor build completes**\n   - Rust program at `solana/programs/lordofrngs/` ✓ exists\n   - lib.rs declares program module ✓ exists\n   - Cargo.toml has `crate-type = [\"cdylib\", \"lib\"]` ✓ configured\n\n2. **Run IDL sync**\n   ```bash\n   ./scripts/sync-idl\n   # Will copy lordofrngs.json and lordofrngs.ts to packages/anchor-client/src/\n   ```\n\n3. **Update anchor-client/src/index.ts**\n   ```typescript\n   import LordofrngsIDL from \"./lordofrngs.json\" with { type: \"json\" };\n   export type { Lordofrngs } from \"./lordofrngs.js\";\n   export { LordofrngsIDL };\n   ```\n\n4. **Consumers import as**\n   ```typescript\n   import { LordofrngsIDL, type Lordofrngs } from \"@rng-utopia/anchor-client\";\n   ```\n\nAll files follow identical structure — no special handling needed beyond syncing the generated artifacts."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ab652f8 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 57696\ntool_uses: 38\nduration_ms: 101354</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f4281aa2-334c-41cb-8346-1f9da2569415","uuid":"93ce98c2-e9a8-4951-be09-06533be57604","tool_use_resul